	Subordinated debt




	On June 26, 2014, Customers Bank closed a private placement transaction in which it issued


	$110.0 million


	 of fixed-to-floating rate subordinated notes due 2029. The subordinated notes bear interest at an annual fixed rate of


	6.125%


	 until June 26, 2024, and interest is paid semiannually. From June 26, 2024, the subordinated notes will bear an annual interest rate equal to three-month LIBOR plus


	344.3


	 basis points until maturity on June 26, 2029. Customers Bank has the ability to call the subordinated notes, in whole or in part, at a redemption price equal to


	100%


	 of the principal balance at certain times on or after June 26, 2024.




	The subordinated notes qualify as Tier 2 capital for regulatory capital purposes.








